speech.p:
Not less than once per year the Postmaster-General shall—


(a) cause to be made a list of all householders shown on Post Office records as not possessing a television licence;

(b) cause a communication to be sent to such householders requiring confirmation that no television set is in use;

(c) instruct Post Office staff to visit those householders from whom no satisfactory reply is received.—[Mr. Bryan.]
